                    <li>Medicines include prescriptions for motion sickness medicines such as antacids, pain relief and the use of fever reducers. </li>
                    <li>Napkins, plastic bags, and a new set of clothes for children who are susceptible towards motion sickness. </li>
                </ul>
                <h2 class="text-justify">13. Bring snacks to the party. </h2>
                <p class="text-justify">This suggestion to fly with kids is so vital that I have to mention it over and over again! According to me, snacks are the number. 1 way to keep kids at ease and content during flights. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">Bring snacks from home an excellent way to cut down on the costs related to food purchases at the airport or aboard. </p>
                <p class="text-justify">Another tip for planning Do not forget to pack a variety of snacks for your return trip back home! I usually pack two separate Ziplock bags of snacks: one for the journey 'there as well as one to take home for the return journey. </p>
